Description: Framework for evaluating and learning realistic policies based on doubly robust loss functions. Policy learning methods include Q-learning <doi:10.1201/9780429192692>, (doubly robust) V-restricted Q-learning <doi:10.1515/ijb-2015-0052> and (doubly robust) sequential policy tree learning <doi:10.48550/arXiv.1810.04778>.
